Answer: There are 30 teams in Major League Baseball (MLB). These teams
        are divided into two leagues: the American League (AL) and the National
        League (NL). All but one team are based in the United States; the
        Toronto Blue Jays
        are the only MLB team from Canada.

The New York Yankees hold the record for the most World Series wins of
        any team in the MLB, having claimed the championship title 27 times.

Answer: Each MLB team plays 162 games in the regular season before the
        playoffs begin. Opening Day for the MLB is generally in April, though it
        can vary depending on various circumstances. For example, in 2025,
        Opening Day was in March.

The MLB postseason concludes at the end of October or early November
        with the
        World Series.

Answer: The World Series is a best-of-seven matchup. The first team to
        win four games against their opponent wins the Commissioner's Trophy.

The 2025 World Series features the
        Los Angeles Dodgers
        and the Toronto Blue Jays. The Dodgers defeated the New York Yankees in
        the 2024 World Series, winning four games to the Yankees' one. The Blue
        Jays have not appeared in the World Series since 1993, when they beat
        the Philadelphia Phillies four games to two.
